# Portal Core Integration Tests

## Purpose

Define and test critical Portal user flows. The seat assignment flow is the most important user journey.

## Code is Functional WHEN...

### Dashboard Tests

```javascript
test("Onboarding tutorial visible for new users", async ({ page }) => {
  // Clear any stored state
  await page.evaluate(() => localStorage.clear());
  await page.goto("/portal/index.html");

  await expect(page.locator("#onboarding")).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.locator(".onboarding-progress")).toBeVisible();
});

test("Onboarding dismisses and persists", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.evaluate(() => localStorage.clear());
  await page.goto("/portal/index.html");

  await page.click("#dismiss-onboarding");
  await expect(page.locator("#onboarding")).not.toBeVisible();

  // Reload and verify still hidden
  await page.reload();
  await expect(page.locator("#onboarding")).not.toBeVisible();
});

test("License cards show correct utilization", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/index.html");

  // Card with 42/50 seats should show 84%
  const card = page.locator(".license-card").first();
  await expect(card.locator(".utilization-bar")).toHaveCSS("width", /84%/);
});
```

### Seat Assignment Flow Tests (Critical Path)

```javascript
test("Complete seat assignment flow", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/seats/assign.html");

  // Step 1: Select license
  await expect(page.locator("[data-step=1]")).toHaveClass(/active/);
  await page.click("[data-testid=license-option]:first-child");
  await page.click("[data-testid=continue]");

  // Step 2: Select user
  await expect(page.locator("[data-step=2]")).toHaveClass(/active/);
  await page.click("[data-testid=user-option]:first-child");
  await page.click("[data-testid=continue]");

  // Step 3: Confirm
  await expect(page.locator("[data-step=3]")).toHaveClass(/active/);
  await expect(page.locator(".confirmation-summary")).toContainText("Premium");
  await page.click("[data-testid=confirm-assign]");

  // Step 4: Success
  await expect(page.locator("[data-testid=success-message]")).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.locator("[data-testid=success-message]")).toContainText("Seat Assigned");
});

test("Back button navigates to previous step", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/seats/assign.html");

  // Go to step 2
  await page.click("[data-testid=license-option]:first-child");
  await page.click("[data-testid=continue]");

  // Go back
  await page.click("[data-testid=back]");
  await expect(page.locator("[data-step=1]")).toHaveClass(/active/);
});

test("Cannot proceed without selection", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/seats/assign.html");

  // Continue button should be disabled
  await expect(page.locator("[data-testid=continue]")).toBeDisabled();

  // Select a license
  await page.click("[data-testid=license-option]:first-child");
  await expect(page.locator("[data-testid=continue]")).toBeEnabled();
});

test("No seats available shows message", async ({ page }) => {
  // Use scenario with no available seats
  await page.goto("/portal/seats/assign.html?scenario=no-seats");

  await expect(page.locator(".no-seats-message")).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.locator("[data-testid=continue]")).not.toBeVisible();
});

test("User already has seat shows warning", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/seats/assign.html");

  // Select license
  await page.click("[data-testid=license-option]:first-child");
  await page.click("[data-testid=continue]");

  // Select user who already has a seat
  await page.click("[data-testid=user-option][data-has-seat=true]");

  await expect(page.locator(".existing-seat-warning")).toBeVisible();
});

test("Can invite new user instead of selecting", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/seats/assign.html");
  await page.click("[data-testid=license-option]:first-child");
  await page.click("[data-testid=continue]");

  // Fill invite form instead of selecting
  await page.fill("[data-invite-email]", "newteacher@school.edu");
  await page.fill("[data-invite-first]", "New");
  await page.fill("[data-invite-last]", "Teacher");

  await expect(page.locator("[data-testid=continue]")).toBeEnabled();
});
```

### License List Tests

```javascript
test("Filters update visible cards", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/licenses/index.html");

  await page.selectOption("[data-filter=type]", "premium");

  // All visible cards should be Premium
  const badges = await page.locator(".license-card .badge").allTextContents();
  expect(badges.every(b => b.includes("Premium"))).toBe(true);
});

test("Empty filter state shows message", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/portal/licenses/index.html");

  // Apply filter that matches nothing
  await page.selectOption("[data-filter=status]", "expired");

  await expect(page.locator(".empty-state")).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.locator(".empty-state")).toContainText("No licenses match");
});
```

## Edge Cases / Pointy Bits

### Dashboard
- Org with only expired licenses? (show renewal prompts prominently)
- User with no admin permissions? (hide admin-only quick actions)
- All onboarding steps complete? (hide tutorial entirely)

### Seat Assignment
- License expires during assignment flow? (warn, allow completion)
- User already has seat from DIFFERENT pool? (allow, explain upgrade path)
- Invite email already in org? (detect, offer to select existing user)
- Invalid email format? (inline validation before continue)
- Network error on submit? (retry button, don't lose selections)

### License Cards
- License expiring TODAY? (prominent warning styling)
- 100% utilization? (different color, no "Assign" CTA)
- Custom duration (not 1/3/5 year)? (show actual date range)

## Acceptance Criteria

This bead is DONE when:
- [ ] Complete seat assignment flow passes
- [ ] All edge cases documented
- [ ] Error states tested
- [ ] No race conditions in multi-step flow

# Configure vite.config.js for Multi-Page HTML

## Goal

Set up Vite to handle multiple HTML entry points (one per page) and configure proper build output structure.

## Implementation

### Create vite.config.js

```javascript
// laravel-crm-mockups/vite.config.js
import { defineConfig } from "vite";
import { resolve } from "path";
import { glob } from "glob";

// Find all HTML files in src/
const htmlFiles = glob.sync("src/**/*.html");

// Build input object for multi-page
const input = htmlFiles.reduce((entries, file) => {
  const name = file.replace("src/", "").replace(".html", "");
  entries[name] = resolve(__dirname, file);
  return entries;
}, {});

export default defineConfig({
  root: "src",
  base: "./",  // Relative paths for GitHub Pages deployment

  build: {
    outDir: "../dist",
    emptyOutDir: true,
    rollupOptions: {
      input: {
        // Admin pages
        "admin/index": resolve(__dirname, "src/admin/index.html"),
        "admin/organizations/index": resolve(__dirname, "src/admin/organizations/index.html"),
        "admin/organizations/detail": resolve(__dirname, "src/admin/organizations/detail.html"),
        // ... more pages added as they're created

        // Portal pages
        "portal/index": resolve(__dirname, "src/portal/index.html"),
        "portal/licenses/index": resolve(__dirname, "src/portal/licenses/index.html"),
        // ... more pages added as they're created
      }
    }
  },

  server: {
    port: 5173,
    open: "/admin/index.html"  // Open admin dashboard by default
  },

  resolve: {
    alias: {
      "@": resolve(__dirname, "src"),
      "@shared": resolve(__dirname, "src/shared"),
      "@admin": resolve(__dirname, "src/admin"),
      "@portal": resolve(__dirname, "src/portal")
    }
  }
});
```

---

## Configuration Explained

### `root: "src"`

Sets the project root to src/ so that:
- Dev server serves from src/
- Paths in HTML are relative to src/
- Cleaner import paths

### `base: "./"`

Uses relative paths in production build so mockups can be:
- Opened directly as files (file://)
- Hosted on any subdirectory
- Deployed to GitHub Pages

### `build.rollupOptions.input`

Explicitly lists all HTML entry points because:
- Vite needs to know which files to process
- Each becomes a separate chunk
- Enables code splitting per page

### `resolve.alias`

Provides clean import paths:
```javascript
// Instead of: import "@/../../shared/js/modal.js"
import "@shared/js/modal.js"
```

---

## Dynamic Input Discovery (Alternative)

If manually listing pages is tedious, use glob:

```javascript
import { glob } from "glob";

const htmlFiles = glob.sync("src/**/*.html", { cwd: __dirname });
const input = Object.fromEntries(
  htmlFiles.map(file => [
    file.replace("src/", "").replace(".html", ""),
    resolve(__dirname, file)
  ])
);
```

**Note**: Requires `npm install -D glob`

---

## PostCSS Integration

Vite automatically detects `postcss.config.js` (created in next task).

---

## Verification

```bash
# Start dev server
npm run dev
# Should see: Local: http://localhost:5173/admin/index.html

# Build for production
npm run build
# Should create dist/ folder with all HTML files
ls dist/admin dist/portal

# Preview production build
npm run preview
```

---

## Files Created

- `laravel-crm-mockups/vite.config.js`

---

## Common Issues

1. **HTML not found**: Ensure paths in input object are correct
2. **Alias not resolving**: Restart dev server after config change
3. **Build fails**: Check all referenced files exist

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] vite.config.js exists with multi-page config
- [ ] `npm run dev` starts server on port 5173
- [ ] Navigating between pages works in dev mode
- [ ] `npm run build` creates dist/ with proper structure
- [ ] Production paths work (no 404s)

# Phase 1: Shared Infrastructure

## Purpose

Build the reusable foundation that ALL pages in both Admin CRM and Organization Portal will use. This includes:
- Shared JavaScript components (modal, dropdown, toast, tabs)
- Seed data fixtures (JSON files simulating API responses)
- State management (LocalStorage with fallback)
- Global UI patterns (command palette, notifications)

## Why Shared Infrastructure?

Without shared components:
- Each page would reinvent modals, dropdowns, etc.
- Inconsistent behavior across pages
- No demo data to populate tables/cards
- No state persistence between page loads

This phase creates the "component library" and "data layer" for mockups.

---

## Components to Build

### 1. Modal System (`shared/js/components/modal.js`)

```javascript
// API:
Modal.open(id)       // Opens modal by ID
Modal.close(id)      // Closes modal
Modal.closeAll()     // Closes all modals

// Features:
// - Backdrop click to close
// - Escape key to close
// - Focus trap (accessibility)
// - Body scroll lock when open
// - Transition animations
```

**Accessibility Requirements**:
- `role="dialog"` and `aria-modal="true"`
- Focus trapped within modal
- Return focus to trigger on close

### 2. Dropdown System (`shared/js/components/dropdown.js`)

```javascript
// API:
Dropdown.toggle(id)  // Toggles dropdown visibility
Dropdown.open(id)
Dropdown.close(id)
Dropdown.closeAll()

// Features:
// - Click outside to close
// - Escape key to close
// - Keyboard navigation (arrow keys)
// - Support nested menus
```

**Use Cases**:
- User profile menu
- Table row actions menu
- Filter dropdowns
- Notification dropdown

### 3. Tab System (`shared/js/components/tabs.js`)

```javascript
// API:
Tabs.activate(tabId, panelId)

// Features:
// - URL hash synchronization (detail.html#billing)
// - Keyboard navigation (left/right arrows)
// - ARIA attributes for accessibility
```

**Use Cases**:
- Organization detail tabs (Overview, Licenses, Billing, Users, Activity)
- License detail tabs (Seats, Activity, Billing)
- Settings pages

### 4. Toast Notifications (`shared/js/components/toast.js`)

```javascript
// API:
Toast.show({ message, type, duration })
// type: "success" | "error" | "warning" | "info"
// duration: milliseconds (default 5000)

// Features:
// - Stack multiple toasts
// - Auto-dismiss with progress indicator
// - Swipe/click to dismiss
// - Position: bottom-right
```

**Use Cases**:
- Form submission success
- Error messages
- Action confirmations

### 5. Command Palette (`shared/js/components/commandPalette.js`)

```javascript
// API:
CommandPalette.open()
CommandPalette.close()
CommandPalette.search(query)
CommandPalette.registerActions(actions)

// Features:
// - Cmd+K / Ctrl+K to open
// - Fuzzy search across actions
// - Recent searches
// - Keyboard navigation
// - Categories (Navigation, Actions, Search)
```

**Actions to Register**:
- Navigate to any page
- Quick actions (New Organization, Assign Seat, etc.)
- Search entities (organizations, users, licenses)

### 6. Notification Dropdown (`shared/js/components/notifications.js`)

```javascript
// Features:
// - Bell icon with unread count badge
// - Dropdown with notification list
// - Mark as read (individual and all)
// - Categories: Alerts, Updates, System
// - Link to notification settings
```

