## State Management

### `shared/js/state.js`

```javascript
// Wrapper for localStorage with in-memory fallback (for private browsing)
const memoryStore = {};

export const storage = {
  get: (key) => {
    try {
      return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(`crm_${key}`));
    } catch {
      return memoryStore[key];
    }
  },
  set: (key, value) => {
    try {
      localStorage.setItem(`crm_${key}`, JSON.stringify(value));
    } catch {
      memoryStore[key] = value;
    }
  },
  remove: (key) => {
    try {
      localStorage.removeItem(`crm_${key}`);
    } catch {
      delete memoryStore[key];
    }
  }
};

// Impersonation state (Admin viewing as Organization)
export const impersonation = {
  get: () => storage.get("impersonation"),
  set: (orgId, orgName) => storage.set("impersonation", { orgId, orgName, startedAt: Date.now() }),
  clear: () => storage.remove("impersonation")
};

// Demo scenarios via URL param: ?scenario=at-risk
export const getScenario = () => new URLSearchParams(window.location.search).get("scenario") || "happy-path";
```

### Demo Scenarios

| Scenario | Description | Use Case |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `happy-path` | Normal data, healthy metrics | Default view |
| `at-risk` | Expiring licenses, failed payments | Test alert states |
| `new-org` | Empty states, onboarding visible | Test empty UX |
| `large-data` | 500+ rows | Test table performance |

Access via URL: `index.html?scenario=at-risk`

